232
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:13,440
Hey.

233
00:16:13,820 --> 00:16:15,410
I mean it.

234
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:22,630
Lin.

235
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:29,160
Let me ask you something.

236
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:33,700
If I ask you for a second chance now,

237
00:16:36,010 --> 00:16:37,140
would it be too late?

238
00:16:42,650 --> 00:16:43,740
You know what, Tong?

239
00:16:45,740 --> 00:16:47,490
I’ve heard that,

240
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:51,160
the prime time in love

241
00:16:54,260 --> 00:16:57,360
is the time before two people decide to be in a relationship.

242
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:01,700
Because once you get into the relationship,

243
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:06,670
the feelings that were there before you date

244
00:17:07,450 --> 00:17:08,640
would disappear.

245
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:17,740
So I want to keep the good feelings between us the way it is.

246
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:25,080
Oh.

247
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:27,600
Then I’m in trouble.

248
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:58,800
But because of that,

249
00:18:01,020 --> 00:18:03,790
