She keeps switching up.

552
00:34:40,560 --> 00:34:43,180
She wouldn’t see anything all the way through.

553
00:34:44,070 --> 00:34:45,680
She’s probably trying to find her identity.

554
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:47,500
I can’t let that slide.

555
00:34:47,520 --> 00:34:49,500
I’ll have to talk to her when she gets back.

556
00:34:49,950 --> 00:34:51,500
Aw.

557
00:34:51,540 --> 00:34:54,320
You’re stricter than Pa and Ma.

558
00:34:54,530 --> 00:34:55,940
We can’t let that slide, Ma.

559
00:34:56,040 --> 00:35:00,180
Someone like Ton Liu will definitely get carried away if we’re not strict with her.

560
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:04,160
Come on, just let her live her teenage life.

561
00:35:06,530 --> 00:35:10,640
By the way, will you proceed with your further studies right away?

562
00:35:18,120 --> 00:35:19,040
Is anything wrong?

563
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:25,120
The thing is, I think I will put aside my studies for now.

564
00:35:28,900 --> 00:35:29,640
Why?

565
00:35:37,420 --> 00:35:38,490
It’s about Petch.

566
00:35:44,850 --> 00:35:45,290
Petch?

567
00:36:03,088 --> 00:36:03,720
Lin.

568
00:36:05,864 --> 00:36:08,056
Do you believe in a parallel universe?

569
00:36:10,672 --> 00:36:11,784
Perhaps,

570
00:36:14,304 --> 00:36:15,472
in another universe

571
00:36:18,688 --> 00:36:20,344
we are together.

572
00:36:26,112 --> 00:36:27,720
I’m envious of them.

573
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:53,896
THIS IS THE STORY OF TONG AND LIN IN THE PARALLEL UNIVERSE.

574
00:36:56,224 --> 00:37:00,224
I’m Tong, a boy from Sukhothai who’s the luckiest man in the universe.

575
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:01,584
Why?

576
00:37:07,050 --> 00:37:09,856
That’s because I get to be Lin’s boyfriend now,

577
00:37:12,008 --> 00:37:14,520
after we almost broke up when I was in my first year of university

578
00:37:14,560 --> 00:37:16,608
because I was always acting so childishly.

579
00:37:25,656 --> 00:37:26,856
How was today?

580
00:37:26,880 --> 00:37:27,656
Was it tiring?

581
00:37:28,232 --> 00:37:29,224
Yes.

582
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:31,480
But not anymore.

583
00:37:32,656 --> 00:37:33,544
You’re exaggerating.

584
00:37:34,520 --> 00:37:35,432
Hold on.

585
00:37:35,904 --> 00:37:36,792
- Why? - 	We can’t get in yet.

586
00:37:43,952 --> 00:37:44,816
Hey!

587
00:37:45,368 --> 00:37:47,050
You’re so bold now.

588
00:37:47,088 --> 00:37:49,050
You’re not shy like when you were younger.

589
00:37:49,344 --> 00:37:50,864
Because I’m all grown up now.

590
00:37:50,992 --> 00:37:52,048
Come on.

591
00:37:53,248 --> 00:37:53,872
Hurry up.

592
00:37:58,992 --> 00:37:59,624
There.

593
00:38:00,208 --> 00:38:00,720
That’s it?

594
00:38:02,608 --> 00:38:04,168
One more time.

595
00:38:04,192 --> 00:38:04,680
Please?

596
00:38:04,712 --> 00:38:05,632
No.

597
00:38:05,656 --> 00:38:06,224
Please, Lin.

598
00:38:06,248 --> 00:38:06,600
No.

599
00:38:06,632 --> 00:38:07,368
I’m going inside.

600
00:38:11,128 --> 00:38:11,744
Hey!

601
00:38:12,088 --> 00:38:13,808
Nobody sees.

602
00:38:15,672 --> 00:38:16,640
Get inside the house.

603
00:38:25,688 --> 00:38:28,304
(Tong’s Diary.)

604
00:38:42,680 --> 00:38:43,440
Babe.

605
00:38:44,208 --> 00:38:45,560
I got you some instant noodles.

606
00:38:48,312 --> 00:38:49,976
I was hungry.

607
00:38:50,752 --> 00:38:52,056
You’re so lovely.

608
00:38:58,824 --> 00:39:01,050
Let’s see.

609
00:39:04,152 --> 00:39:06,176
This reminds me of Uncle Khai’s.

610
00:39:06,368 --> 00:39:08,392
Mine is better than Uncle Khai’s.

611
00:39:08,944 --> 00:39:09,520
Really?

612
00:39:09,896 --> 00:39:10,936
If you don’t trust me then don’t eat it.

613
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:12,264
Aw, no, I’ll eat it.

614
00:39:18,200 --> 00:39:19,096
Blow it before you eat.

615
00:39:27,664 --> 00:39:28,824
This is yummy.

616
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:32,176
As yummy as Uncle Khai’s.

617
00:39:32,304 --> 00:39:33,840
It reminds me of the old days.

618
00:39:34,272 --> 00:39:35,600
You’re exaggerating again.

619
00:39:36,032 --> 00:39:37,544
They’re instant noodles, all the same,

620
00:39:37,576 --> 00:39:39,050
I just added some boiled eggs.

621
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:44,816
Because it’s the same, it reminds me of my friends,

622
00:39:48,816 --> 00:39:49,824
my family,

623
00:39:51,660 --> 00:39:53,280
the time when I was a child,

624
00:39:55,530 --> 00:39:57,144
and also of…

625
00:40:02,944 --> 00:40:03,968
Of what?

626
00:40:15,184 --> 00:40:16,352
Of our first love.

627
00:40:25,392 --> 00:40:27,336
Have your instant noodles.

628
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:32,304
Let’s see.

629
00:40:32,312 --> 00:40:33,176
Ouch, my hands hurt.

630
00:40:34,264 --> 00:40:35,768
Why? Why did your hands hurt?

631
00:40:35,936 --> 00:40:36,792
My hands hurt so I can’t eat.

632
00:40:37,336 --> 00:40:38,984
- Come, I’ll feed you. - I can’t eat.

633
00:40:39,008 --> 00:40:39,968
- Blow it first. - 	I can’t eat.

634
00:40:41,016 --> 00:40:41,904
Ouch, my mouth hurts.

635
00:40:47,864 --> 00:40:49,050
Yum!

636
00:40:56,256 --> 00:40:57,488
Good job!

637
00:40:57,500 --> 00:40:58,168
How was it?

638
00:40:58,192 --> 00:40:58,970
So yummy.

639
00:41:04,750 --> 00:41:08,740
(After graduating, I get to live the life of an adult.)

640
00:41:09,390 --> 00:41:11,800
(I get the taste of being unemployed.)

641
00:41:11,830 --> 00:41:13,920
You? Studying abroad? First, try graduating within this year.

642
00:41:14,650 --> 00:41:15,580
What are you doing, Tong?

643
00:41:16,570 --> 00:41:18,570
Doing something an unemployed person does, Dad.

644
00:41:19,350 --> 00:41:21,340
You’re just like your Mom.

645
00:41:22,160 --> 00:41:23,200
Who are you talking crap about?

646
00:41:23,680 --> 00:41:25,200
Who are you talking crap about?

647
00:41:25,520 --> 00:41:26,640
(But then suddenly,)

648
00:41:26,670 --> 00:41:27,600
(Nonthawat Kiatpeera)

649
00:41:28,010 --> 00:41:29,890
(Lin poked a pen on my back and woke me up.)
